obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_835  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The dopamine transporter is an integral membrane protein of the postsynaptic membrane.\n\nPre-embedding immunogold and immunoperoxidase labelling demonstrates DAT-immunoreactivity predominantly along the plasma membrane in dendrites and dendritic spines (Fig. 1-3). The majority of the DAT-immunoreactivity was localized to tyrosine-hydroxylase positive neurons.\n\nThe DAT antiserum is a polyclonal antiserum directed against a synthetic peptide (aa42-59; LTNSTLINPPQTPVEAQE). The specificity of the antibody was demonstrated in a previous study (See reference 1). No KO-control.. Experimental description: Twelve adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (250-400 gm) were anesthetized..." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
